<span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Doria Rosen</strong></span>

<a href="http://oia.publish.uic.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/126/files/2014/05/D.-Rosen.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-567" src="http://oia.publish.uic.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/126/files/2014/05/D.-Rosen.jpg" alt="D. Rosen" width="126" height="170" /></a>Doria was born in New York City on September 7, 1950. After attending local public schools she graduated from Vassar College in 1972 with an A.B. in psychology and a minor in education. In 1975 she received a J.D. from Hofstra University Law School. She was admitted to the New York State Bar in 1976, the Military Court of Appeals in 1976, and to the California State Bar in 1977.

