<span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Deborah Schwartz</strong></span>

<a href="http://oia.publish.uic.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/126/files/2014/04/D.-Schwartz1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-580" src="http://oia.publish.uic.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/126/files/2014/04/D.-Schwartz1.jpg" alt="D. Schwartz" width="136" height="182" /></a>Deborah Schwartz is a Minister Counselor in the Foreign Service of the U.S. Department of State. She has served as the senior Economic Officer in Mexico, Israel, Taiwan and Nigeria and also as the Deputy Chief of Mission in Honduras. Ms. Schwartz received her B.A. in Latin American Studies and M.B.A. in International Business from The George Washington University in Washington, D.C. She currently serves as Diplomat in Residence at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.

