<span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Ronald Godard</strong></span>

<a href="http://oia.publish.uic.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/126/files/2014/04/R.-Godard1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-582" src="http://oia.publish.uic.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/126/files/2014/04/R.-Godard1.jpg" alt="R. Godard" width="136" height="177" /></a>Ambassador Ronald Godard, a Minister Counselor in the Foreign Service, has served in U.S. Embassies in Panama, Nicaragua, Costa Rica, Chile, Argentina, Turkey, and as U.S. Ambassador to Guyana.  He has served under eight presidents. Mr. Godard received a B.A. in History and a M.A. in Latin American Studies from the University of Texas.

